Description: early 70s pre serial number Ibanez 2451the most 'Gibson like' L6-S there is!all maple body, set neck, exact replica wiringsadly it has been modified by previous ownerswho decided 3 pickups were better than 2 and drilled a gaping cavity into the body - with some holes going all the way throughthis is covered by the addition to the pick guard, but the holes are still visible on the backthe original neck pickup has gone - currently replaced by a Gotoh humbucker that reads 8.3k, which matches the bridge pickupA kill switch has also been added, and the machines have been replaced with vintage West German Schallersapart from that everything appears to be original Cosmetically it is in pretty good nickthere is some pitting on the bridge, tailpiece and pick up coversminor dings on the body and some extra holes near the rear strap pinthere are also some cracks in the varnish on the underside of the neck near the nut - looks like it happened when the nut was changed, as the neck is stable All in all it is a very playable guitar I will ship Worldwide, fully insured in the TKL hard case picturedplease use the eBay calculator as a guide and wait for final invoice And check out my other listings for more cool vintage Jap guitars and basses
